a-hidden="true" class="rah-static rah-static--height-zero SidebarWrapper" style="height:0;overflow:hidden"><div><div class="sc-2e8621ab-0 jwmryO sc-3ddd79c0-7 rkpEx"><a href="/users/lachlan-summers" class="sc-2e8621ab-1 jexetL">Lachlan Summers</a><span><p>is a postdoctoral fellow at the Max Planck Institute for the History of Science in Berlin, where he is a member of the ‘Time Scales: Historicizing Deep Time’ working group.</p></span></div><br/><div class="sc-3ddd79c0-9 eACYrZ"><p>Edited by<a href="/users/cameron-allan-mckean" class="sc-2e8621ab-1 jexetL">Cameron Allan McKean</a></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-114c07c9-0 iNdsQY"><span>3,800<!-- --> words</span><span class="sc-114c07c9-2 hRWhru"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" width="17" height="17" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" data-cy="icon-aeon-save" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M17 3H7c-1.1 0-1.99.9-1.99 2L5 21l7-3 7 3V5c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 15l-5-2.18L7 18V5h10v13z"></path></svg><span>Save</span></span></div><br/><div class="sc-50e6fb3a-1 jUPTLs"><a class="sc-45649ee9-0 lfcsbM sc-50e6fb3a-0 gZdfWA" href="/syndication?article_slug=the-earthquakes-that-shook-mexico-citys-sense-of-time&amp;article_name=When%20does%20after%20begin?&amp;author=Lachlan%20Summers&amp;date=15%20December%202023"><span class="sc-45649ee9-1 cacrwE">Syndicate this <!-- -->essay</span></a></div><div class="sc-c3e98e6e-0 bSqqMf sc-3ddd79c0-13 kNGStK"><div class="sc-c3e98e6e-0 bSqqMf"><div><br/></div><div class="sc-531dc212-0 grcCCz"><div><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" width="20px" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" data-cy="icon-aeon-email" aria-hidden="true" class="sc-531dc212-1 dkebQC"><path d="M22 6c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v12c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h16c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V6zm-2 0l-8 5-8-5h16zm0 12H4V8l8 5 8-5v10z"></path></svg><span class="sc-531dc212-2 gjonPf">Email</span></div><div><svg viewBox="0 