-hunter-npg.jpg","alt":"","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"History of science","slug":"history-of-science"},"topics":[{"slug":"ethics","title":"Ethics"},{"slug":"history-of-science","title":"History of science"},{"slug":"bioethics","title":"Bioethics"}],"section":{"title":"Science","slug":"science"},"createdAt":"2023-10-23T10:07:45Z"},{"id":"6023","title":"Citizens","slug":"a-story-about-who-grows-up-and-who-goes-away-in-1970s-england","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"A story about who grows up and who goes away in 1970s England","standfirstLong":"Devon, 1970s: I’m a rector’s son, hanging out with Boz the biker. My life is about to open up – what does it promise for him?","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":"white","cardPlayIconColor":"white","alignX":"right","alignY":"center","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"179791","displayName":"Tim Pears"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/4dcc05b1-c778-4ae5-bbe8-ee0fa817ff2e/test-essay-new-gettyimages-1196680416.jpg","alt":"Three motorcyclists are riding on an empty road winding through English moorland beneath a blue sky","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Stories and literature","slug":"stories-literature"},"topics":[{"slug":"stories-literature","title":"Stories and literature"},{"slug":"demography-migration","title":"Demography and migration"},{"slug":"love-friendship","title":"Love and friendship"}],"section":{"title":"Culture","slug":"culture"},"createdAt":"2023-09-25T13:04:28Z"},{"id":"6111","title":"A glimpse of the world’s heart","slug":"on-the-intangible-border-of-the-kogis-sacred-mountains","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"On the intangible border of the Kogi’s sacred mountains","standfirstLong":"I wanted to visit Colombia’s sacred mountains. But there are some places we cannot go – and some things we cannot know","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"se